class FontAwesome5 extends Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    props.setTitle('Font Awesome 5 - Icons')

    this.search = this.search.bind(this)

    this.state = {
      icons: iconList.slice(0)
    }
  }

  getIconClass(icon) {
    return `.${icon[0]}.fa-${icon[1]}`
  }

  search(e) {
    const val = String(e.target.value).replace(/^\s+|\s+$/g, '')

    if (!val) {
      this.setState({
        icons: iconList.slice(0)
      })
      return
    }

    this.setState({
      icons: iconList.reduce((res, icon) => {
        if (icon[1].indexOf(val) !== -1) res.push(icon)
        return res
      }, [])
    })
  }

  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <h4 className="font-weight-bold py-3 mb-4">
          <span className="text-muted font-weight-light">Icons /</span> Font Awesome 5
        </h4>

        <hr className="container-m-nx border-light mt-0 mb-4" />

        <div className="py-2 my-4 mx-auto" style={{ maxWidth: '300px' }}>
          <InputGroup>
            <InputGroup.Prepend>
              <InputGroup.Text><i className="ion ion-ios-search"></i></InputGroup.Text>
            </InputGroup.Prepend>
            <FormControl placeholder="Search..." onInput={this.search} />
          </InputGroup>
        </div>

        <div className="text-center">
          {this.state.icons.map(icon => (
            <Card
              key={`${icon[0]}${icon[1]}`}
              data-title={this.getIconClass(icon)}
              className="icon-example icon-example-fa d-inline-flex justify-content-center align-items-center my-2 mx-2">
              <i className={`d-block ${icon[0]} fa-${icon[1]}`}></i>
            </Card>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>
    )
  }
}

export default FontAwesome5
